pulltitle: Require js
pullsbody:
Here I spited the application in different filles so every controller/directive can be a stand alone file, this makes the application more readable and it loads the js files asynchronously.
I change nothing in the logic of the application here, but only the way it loads.

Here is an example of this practice:
https://github.com/tnajdek/angular-requirejs-seed/tree/master/app/js
pull_commit_message: Spited the application on smaller files, and bootstrap the application via requireJS
